properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 9 at 11:55AM CST until January 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTRY MIX OF FREEZING DRIZZLE AND SNOW EXPECTED TODAY...

.Low pressure approaching from the Northern Plains will produce a
mixture of snow, sleet, freezing rain and freezing drizzle across
the region. While snow and ice accumulations are expected to be
relatively light, driving conditions will be hazardous in some
areas. The threat of freezing precipitation will taper off over
central and eastern Wisconsin later this afternoon as road
temperatures warm above freezing.

* WHAT...A mix of light freezing rain, sleet and snow. Ice
accumulation of less than one-tenth of an inch. Little snow
accumulation expected.

* WHERE...Menominee, Marathon and Shawano Counties.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on icy road conditions. Hazardous travel
conditions will continue through the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for Wisconsin can be obtained by
calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST THIS EVENING
